[src:spring-boot/spring-framework] `DispatcherServlet` chooses an appropriate controller and forwards the request to it.
[src:spring-boot/spring-framework] The `Controller` processes the particular request and generates a result.
[src:spring-boot/spring-framework] This information needs to be formatted in HTML or any front-end technology like Jakarta Server Pages (also known as JSP) or Thymeleaf.
[src:spring-boot/spring-framework] All of the information is in the `Model` and `View` object.
[src:spring-boot/spring-framework] When the controller is not coupled to a particular view, `DispatcherServlet` finds the actual `View` (such as JSP) with the help of `ViewResolver`.
[src:spring-boot/spring-framework] Spring's Remote Access framework is an abstraction for working with various RPC (remote procedure call)-based technologies available on the Java platform both for client connectivity and marshalling objects on servers.
