[src:spring-boot/spring-framework] Spring Batch executes a series of jobs; a job consists of a number of steps and each step consists of a "READ-PROCESS-WRITE" task or single operation task (tasklet).
[src:spring-boot/spring-framework] A "single" operation task is also known as a tasklet.
[src:spring-boot/spring-framework] It means doing a single task only, like cleaning up the resources before or after a step is started or completed.
[src:spring-boot/spring-framework] The "READ-PROCESS-WRITE" process consists of these steps: "read" data from a resource (comma-separated values (CSV), XML, or database), "process" it, then "write" it to other resources (CSV, XML, or database).
[src:spring-boot/spring-framework] For example, a step may read data from a CSV file, process it, and write it into the database.
[src:spring-boot/spring-framework] Spring Batch provides a number of classes to read/write CSV, XML, and database.
[src:spring-boot/spring-framework] The steps can be chained together to run as a job.
